Blocks.childText: 186 The Ten Blessings. (With chant response.) School. From "Choir and Congregation." Sup't. #2 I. 4 Blessed are the poor in spirit: The Lord is nigh unto them broken heart: And saveth such as be of a contrite spirit. for theirs is the kingdom of that are of a heaven. School. Sup't. II. Blessed are they that mourn: This is my comfort in my af - fliction: For thy word hath quick - en'd me. for they shall be comforted. Sup't. School. III. Blessed are the meek: for they shall inherit the earth. The meek will he guide in judg-ment: And the meek will he teach his way. (Base and Tenor, see chant atove.) Sup't. IV. School. Blessed are they that de hun- ger and thirst after righteous- 6'1 ness: for they shall he filled. He shall receive the blessing from the Lord : And righteousness from the God of his salvation. (Base and Tenor, see chant above.) Sup't. School. V. Blessed are the merciful: for for they shall obtain mercy. He that trusteth in the Lord: Mercy shall com - pass him a bout. (Base and Tenor, see chant above.) Sup't. School. VI. Blessed are the pure in neart: for they shall see God. gold Create in me a clean heart, o God: And renew a right spir-it with - in me. (Base and Tenor, see chant above.) By permission.
